headline.main: RABAUL SET AFIRE BY ALLIED PLANES; Flames Flare in 22 Areas, Lakunai Airdrome Blazes, Grounded Planes Wrecked FUEL DUMPS DESTROYED On Ground in New Guinea, Allied Artillery Blasts Enemy Near Salamaua

lead_paragraph: AT UNITED NATIONS HEADQUARTERS IN AUSTRALIA, Tuesday, Feb. 2 (AP) -- General Douglas MacArthur's airmen carried the fight to the vital Japanese air base at Rabaul, New Britain, in a slashing attack yesterday that left more than twenty-two fires blazing, while intensive Allied patrol activity in the jungles around Mubo-Wau kept the enemy worried.
abstract: US planes blast Lakunai and Rapopo airdromes, Rabaul; Allied patrols aided by artillery harass foe, Mubo-Wau area; Jap drive for Wau discussed; US plane bombs Jap ship; returns to fire it by machine gun; map
